		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			I cannot see how manaburn could be useful to anyone at all, not just endgame wizards.  Face it, it's an entirely useless skill, and nothing they do to it is going to make it an important skill.  It's not even nearly as efficient as using kunark nukes, even kunark lures.<br><br>You say manaburn is fun because it's a big boom.  Well, personally, I'd find it a LOT more fun being useful and needed in xp groups, having a valid function that I could actually fill, rather than having a toy.  I'd rather have people say "wizards are good in groups, they have a high sustained dps that will increase how much xp we get, let's invite that wizard" than "wizards are useless in dps, but they can do one big nuke ever 2.5 hours, and then they stand their bragging like morons, ignoring the fact that they have done minimal damage before it, and even less after it as they are then oom".  People are not so stupid as to believe that wizards are doing great damage in their groups just because they see one big crit every few hours.  It's not fooling anyone, least of all the wizards.<br><br>Manaburn lowers sustained dps and burst dps because it is horribly inefficient.  The only mobs it has any use on at all are those resistant to all spells, including lures, which basically means zun muram.<br><br>It's not really a broken class skill, it's just not a terribly useful one.  All classes have some crappy class skills, this is one of ours.<br><br>I just don't get why people would fight for an ability that lowers both sustained and burst dps when we are already so far behind in these key class defining wizard abilities.  Damage, burst and sustained, should be the 2 class defining abilities of wizards, and those are broken.  That is what needs to be the focus, not some trivial toy like manaburn.<br><br>When the real stuff is fixed, we can look at fixing toys, until then, we need to focus on what will give us value as a class.	
		</td></tr>
