			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=45134'>







<img src="/eq/i/icons/Classes/beserker.gif" border=0 alt=""/></a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=wizardbalance&message.id=2651#M2651">112</a> of 234
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 490 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Here's your manaburn use:</DIV>
<DIV>Your guild is pushing for thier time keys, and now its time to take out coirnav.&nbsp; You have defeated all 3 named and are taking down the big guy.&nbsp; For most pre-time guilds, you will have about 1-2 minutes to make calamari.&nbsp; Even chain nuking, you can expect to still be at 50%+ mana at the end of 1.5 minutes.&nbsp; MB would be the answer to get rid of all that mana in one big burn that could help your guild win.&nbsp; There's your ONE use.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As for everyone whining about them working on manaburn, you are probably the same people that complain that +1 mana regen doesn't make a difference, or that +50 mana doesn't make a difference.&nbsp; What you fail to realize is that even +1 hp upgrades can lead to 11k hps over a long enough time frame.&nbsp; Just because they didn't give us an instant death nuke at level 1 doesn't mean that we're useless.&nbsp; I am a moderately decently geared 70 wizard.&nbsp; Unlike other wizards, I have abandoned the concept of pure DPS for a more utilitarian approach.&nbsp; Currently, there is not another class I have grouped with that can handle casters better than I.&nbsp; Sure bards and chanters have mez, but mez does no damage, consumes mana that could be used for useful things like mezzing mobs that need to be parked and slowing mobs, and also can create aggro issues.&nbsp; Using Spark of Thunder, I can keep any caster mob from getting off any spell.&nbsp; If I were REALLY decently geared, I could couple it with concussion pants and do so without ever stealing aggro.&nbsp; With strong root, I am regularly called on in raid situations to park a certain mob since my guild is short on chanters.&nbsp; I am one of the few wizards that invested in the entire calrena line, and tanks in my guild LOVE it, since they have a little buffer between their spellshields when they are getting hit for 4k dds.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>What do all of these have in common?&nbsp; I have taken a spell or ability that has been largely reguarded as useless, and turned it into a VERY useful situation.&nbsp; How does this apply to manaburn?&nbsp; Well, take the facts:&nbsp; its unresistable and it dumps all your mana for a comparative # of damage, capped at a certain amount.&nbsp; If you guys would stop looking at the fact that it takes all your mana, and realize that it takes all your REMAINING mana, you might realize that a manaburn at FM is asinine anyhow.&nbsp; The real key is to use it properly.&nbsp; If a mob is at 10% health and your clerics/tanks are dropping like flies, what could it hurt to toss a manaburn?&nbsp; It could very well be the difference between a complete wipe and an amazing sucess.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>PLEASE stop complaining when SOE wants to give us a tool.&nbsp; Yes, MB isn't class defining and yes, our fixes shouldn't revolve around MB finally getting attention, but for the love of pete, please stop giving negative feedback.&nbsp; What could SOE possibly want to give us if all we ever do is whine about what we get?&nbsp; Take what we're given, find creative ways to use it, give positive feedback, and if you really don't like it then don't waste your time with it, but PLEASE PLEASE PLEASE don't waste the rest of our time with useless whining that can only result in more (yes MORE) lack of attention to our class.</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>03-22-2005</span> <span class=time_text>02:12 PM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
