			"PLEASE stop complaining when SOE wants to give us a tool.  Yes, MB isn't class defining and yes, our fixes shouldn't revolve around MB finally getting attention, but for the love of pete, please stop giving negative feedback.  What could SOE possibly want to give us if all we ever do is whine about what we get?  Take what we're given, find creative ways to use it, give positive feedback, and if you really don't like it then don't waste your time with it, but PLEASE PLEASE PLEASE don't waste the rest of our time with useless whining that can only result in more (yes MORE) lack of attention to our class."<br><br>We are complaining because the people who are pushing for manaburn changes are taking attention and resources away from the real problems facing our class.  We need SOE to understand that changing manaburn will not make us happy and shut us up.<br><br>The coirnav example doesn't work really.  First of all, it doesn't stack, so only one person could use it.  Second, in the few minutes you have, you can unload enough of your mana to make that manaburn hit for about 4-5k, which is about what a regular nuke hits for anyways, and then if you were off by a bit on the timing, you could keep nuking and do more damage.  Manaburn would reduce your damage on that fight.<br><br>I actually have fought and defeated Coirnav multiple times.  No one in my guild used manaburn.  First of all, if the wizards have full mana when coirnav goes live, they were slacking through the initial waves, which are the most difficult part of the encounter anyways.<br><br>So PLEASE PLEASE PLEASE stop asking for manaburn changes, something that won't do crap for us as a class, and thus ignoring and diverting attention away from the stuff that actually matters.	
