			>
			Gnomish Greetings!<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Boradek-CC wrote:<BR>It's not really a broken class skill, it's just not a terribly useful one. All classes have some crappy class skills, this is one of ours.<BR><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>It is a broken class skill precisely because it is not a useful one.&nbsp; It should be as useful as Lifeburn or Improved Harm Touch.&nbsp; It could be a burst dps utility ability.&nbsp; How they fix it will determine if it can become useful.&nbsp; </P>
<P>Burst dps is the staple of wizardary.&nbsp; Higher end wizards have more AAs, ancient spells, and best focus so they may not have as much use for the ability.&nbsp; Lower end wizards&nbsp;should still&nbsp;be exceptional at burst dps, and this AA could be a fix for us.&nbsp; For example, what if the ability did not take all of your mana?&nbsp; What if it could critical?&nbsp; </P>
<P>There are a lot of potential fixes that might bring Manaburn up to par with some of the other AA abilites given to other classes, and bring the lower tiered wizards in line with them.<BR></P>
