		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			Manaburn:<br><br>I see alot of wizards going crazy over the thought of fixing this. (I use the word fixing with all possible inferance.) <br>There appears to be alot of Anti-Manaburn-Love. "Why this, there are other things to fix, this isn't important, why, why, why, etc, ad infinitum."<br><br>Why fix it?<br><br>Why not? At the moment, it serves no use. It's pointless. It has less of a point than our wizard hats. It's broken. It has been completely, utterly, and brutally nerfed into uselessness.<br>Personally, I would like to use it again and see it do more damage than a single nuke. If Sony think outside the box for a bit, they could make it interesting, and actually of some use again. Win all round as far as I'm concerned.<br><br><br>Are there other things more important to the wizard class that need fixing? Well, yes, most likely. <br>Is this the 'start' of the re-envisionment? Yes. Brenlo, funny feller that he is, said so.<br><br>Wizard sustained DPS needs fixing. <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0><br><br>There you go, I said it. I feel better actually. <br><br>We do nothing else. We are about as focused as you could get, yet we don't excel at our chosen field. Obviously this is a problem. Other classes do comparable damage, have better longevity, utility and pets. We have translocates! <br>I agree, sustained DPS needs looking at. However, I also want Manaburn sorted.<br><br>I've seen loads of wizards moaning something terrible, and I just don't get it. Sony, in a rare move, (sorry SOE), have proposed something bold and fresh.<br>Do we encourage it? No, of course not. We moan like hell and ridicule what they are trying to do in the belief that this will somehow make things go in our favour.<br><br>Personally, I was thankfull. Hey, shoot me for siding with the Man, but I was. Someone in Sony, or someones, have had an epiphany, and thought, "Things need sorting!"<br>Instead of running off changing things without thinking, they have asked their playerbase. We responded. They responded. We whined like kids.<br><br>I'd like to erase the last bit and replace it with, "We gave more feedback in a constructive manner, showing the passion we have for the class."<br>It's not as short and snappy as "We whined like kids," but ultimately, I think it would have more impact.<br><br>I'm sorry if I'm being condecending here, or snotty, or a billion other words which equate to, "Being an arse," but put yourself in their shoes.<br>If you tried like hell to provide your players with what they wanted, and 'This' was the response? What would you do?<br><br><br>Fixing manaburn, is as others have said, a sign that things can change. Not to mention a useless AA becomes perhaps a useful one. It's never going to be unbalancing, and who wants that? It's not the ultimate ability of wizards! Nobody is saying that.<br>Other changes can happen after manaburn if there is a need for them. Manaburn is a good step in the right direction.<br><br>Remember, despite all the arguments, Manaburn did come 1st on the wizard list of issues. Someone wanted it fixed.<br><br><br>K	
