		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>First, the thing about Manaburn in it's original state was that it stacked for explosive DPS - it was THE best dps in the game when you had several wizards unleashed at once. The proposed change doesn't put it back to this, it still won't stack, and thus, it will still be just a toy.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I'm not saying not to fix manaburn, I am saying that SOE should <STRONG>not</STRONG> give us this, and <STRONG>then think</STRONG> we're balanced in the burst dps-department&nbsp;because the change as proposed will do nothing to help us there, since it <STRONG>wont stack.</STRONG> We need bigger manapools, less aggro per nuke, much higher DPS to allow for more concussioning between each nuke. <STRONG>Then, maybe</STRONG> we're going to be where we need to be in the burst DPS department. This change to manaburn is nothing but a shut-up pill for the vocal group of wizards that just wont let the dead horse rest.</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
