		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			The point is that anyone that really believes that manaburn is a major part of the wizard class doesn't understand the class.  They don't understand the problems being experienced today by wizards.<br><br>First of all, your suggestion that claw of vox will fix wizard dps shows a complete lack of understanding of how grave the problem is.  WITH claw of vos, we are at 25% of a rogue's dps at the high end.  Maybe this isn't a problem for lower level wizards such as yourself, but it's a huge problem for endgame players.<br><br>Those of us who are very experienced in this game and have watched our class endure years of uselessness are frustrated out of our mind that we have a chance to ask SOE for what we really need, and people are asking for silly window dressing and ignoring the heart of the matter.<br><br>As for the recast timer, I don't want it removed.  I think it's good.  If it were removed, it would make it impossible to have low hp mobs as guilds would just DT them.  The difference between manaburn and lifeburn is a question of numbers.  Many raiding guilds have 10 wizards on at a raid.  Most of those guilds do not have more than 2 necros per raid, and often 1 or none.  There just aren't that many necros in the endgame, for whatever reason, so they don't present much of an issue.  I spent my share of time farming the crap out of kunark dragons and making plat off it.  I'm sorry you leveled too slow for this, but it was nerfed with good reason.  A manaburn skill without any recast timer is a thing of the past, and should be.<br><br>As for how I know what I know, it's from reading this forum and live chats with devs, as well as people I know who personally know developers.  The recast timer is not being removed.  The only thing that's changing is how much damage manaburn will do, ie. what the cap is.<br><br>What I cannot begin to fathom is why you want to worry about something that won't increase your dps instead of fighting for what would make your class actually useful.  It just screams noob to me.	
		</td></tr>
