		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			Let's take a look at what SOE wrote:<br><br>"We will fix Manaburn.  Our preferred method is to uncap the ability and implement a cap based on the maximum percentage of health you can do in a single hit.  So one of you, facing a million hit point boss mob (fairly common in today’s game) can expect a full manaburn to land for 10s of thousands of points of damage in one hit."<br><br>They make it pretty clear that their preferred method is to uncap the ability.  i.e. the unnerf will change the cap.  There is no mention of removing the reuse timer.<br><br>However, note the wording "ONE of you, facing..."  ONE of us will be able to nuke the mob for 10's of thousands.  Yet another indication that they mean to maintain the 1 manaburn per minute rule.  It's not going anywhere.<br><br>Most of all, I DON'T CARE.  Any changes except the utterly absurd made to manaburn will not appease the angry wizard horde in the slightest.  We want increased sustained and burst dps, and manaburn gives us neither.  SOE, when you make us a viable damage class, then I might care about the bells and whistles.  Until then, don't try to placate us with toys when we need major class surgery.	
