<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=wizardbalance&message.id=2676#M2676">125</a> of 234
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 213 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<br><blockquote><hr>Ammelen wrote:<br>What I cannot begin to fathom is why you want to worry about something that won't increase your dps instead of fighting for what would make your class actually useful. It just screams noob to me. <br><hr></blockquote><br><br><br><br>Can't we worry about both? Wanting to see a broken AA fixed does not make anyone a 'noob'. Manaburn, rightly or wrongly, was voted the primary item the wizard community wanted changing.<br>By your rational, that makes them all noob's.<br><br>People can have an alternate opinion to you, and still be valid players. Belittling them if they don't agree just gets us nowhere.<br><br>Most of us I think have agreed, yes DPS, both burst and sustained needs seriously looking at. As this is the 'start' of the re-envisionment, by all means lets make sure SOE know about it. But there is a right way to go about it.<br>Every post above that went postal in caps, or started being insulting, to SOE and other wizards, did us as a community no service whatsoever.<br>I understand the frustration. I've roaming my wizardly way since the summer of 1999, just after Prexus server came up. I've seen the wizard in its infant stage, (when I didn't realise it could port!), and I've seen it progress. Sometimes it progressed quickly, other times slowly.<br>It has to be said, I've enjoyed it throughout, even when my mage buddy was outnuking me, and his pet was putting  up a better fight than the warrior class.<br><br>The vision for wizards has faltered in places. Focus was shifting away from damage dealing to porting at one stage. Wizards went berzerk, and rightly so.<br>We went through the AE stage, feeling like Gods, and the manaburn stage, again feeling empowered, albeit briefly. We gained familiars, by request. It was the wizard community after all who suggested them.<br>Then we sunk back into mediocrity, providing a bit of DPS and the AE TL home at the end of the raid.<br><br><br>I agree 100% that we need seriously looking at. I've never said different. <br><br><br>However, I also want Manaburn fixing so I can use it once more.<br><br>Yup, I want my nuke-topped cake, and I wish to dine in a wizardly fashion in the company of the mystically powerful.<br><br>So yes, give me DPS in burst, give it to me in sustained, but while you're there, tinkering away, fix manaburn too. <br><br><br>And maybe, just maybe, lets have a long talk with Al'Kabor about that ridiculous spell line he made.<br><br><br>Khaine	
		</td></tr>
